<table border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 width="95%"><TR><td bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><TABLE BORDER=0 cellpadding=4 border=0 cellspacing=1 WIDTH="100%"><TR bgcolor="#000050"><TD COLSPAN=2><CENTER><FONT SIZE="2" COLOR="#FFFFFF" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">T O P I C  &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; R E V I E W</font></CENTER></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">Kraizii</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">Anyone have any opinions?  I've been wearing a Crested helm for a long time and just picked up the SSB.  I'm mulling over whether I should change to the SSB as a day to day helm...  Unfortunately I flip-flop a lot on this one but I think I'm going to stay crested..... but.... the SSB offers more protection..... but is it worth the stats.... but.....</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">Aerafel</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">SSB allllllllll the way. Unless you play a Rogue or don't plan on tanking anytime. The extra AC with the Magic Res. makes it the only choice of a Tank/Puller</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">Blackacid</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">While I think str is nice to have, it's not the be all, end all of stats. In fact, going from a 95-170str changes my damage output so little, it's depressing...<P>Personally, I find the SSB to be a much better helmet. You gaining 3 points of raw AC, +10 to your resistance to magic (which is a damned good thing). That alone was enough to make me switch. Now if I had the hammerhead helm, I'd probably reconsider my choice in equipment.<P>So, if your asking my opinion on it, bank the crested, and put on the SSB. Unless of course, your a human, or woodelf female. Then, by the gods, do us all a favor and get yourself a crown of the froglok kings, and get that trashcan off your head!!!  <IMG SRC="http://boards.stratics.com/forums/smile.gif"><P><P>------------------<BR><B>Tezrian Vrix of Quellious</B><P></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">PackMan97</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">A warriors job is to TAKE DAMAGE! End of discussion. In order to take this damage a warrior needs THREE things. <P>1) AC<BR>2) HIT POINTS<BR>3) +RESISTANCES<P>Any object which can give you all THREE (ie. SSB) is to be worshiped. All bow before the SSB!!!<P>I also think the +MR of the SSB is very underrated. As the premerie tank in Norrath we also need to remember we have to be able to stand up against CASTER NPC's as well. <P>NOTE: EVERY warrior should pick up a BS Mantle (+10 MR), a Split Paw Mask (+5 MR), a Runed Bone Fork (+10 MR) and a Mistmoore Shield (+10 MR)....that's +35 MR you can get easily. Toss in a SSB for another +10MR and maybe some MR rings...we are talking a god like Magic resist before getting buffs. Just laugh at that Rosch Mal Gnoll or Froglyck Wizard as your tear them to shreds.<P>------------------<BR>-Alewuf Shinkicker of Povar<BR>Gem Chopper of the 37thRank<P>"Put on your shinkickers and kick some shin!" -me</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">Kraizii</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">Thanks.  That's exactly what I'm looking for.  I'm gonna miss the extra 6 stones I can carry, but will be happy to be a better tank.<P>Now, I can continue this or start a new one on what to replace a Golden Black Pearl Choker with....  Best just start a new thread and let this one die, unless anyone wants to argue against the SSB for the Crested, in which case, keep it going.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">Zarec the troll</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">magic resist is nice and all but wizards have a lot of cold and fire based spells also.. shamans have cold based spells for DD.. druids fire based..<P>magic resist is only good for root and other less damaging spells, not sure how charm would stack up since it seems to depend heavily on charisma or wisdom also(to defend against mind altering spells).<P>with my druid 50 charisma that VERY green mynthi davissi seems to always charm me (65mr)... yet after the failed attempt some lower level players in the graveyard managed to kill her.. when I asked about the charm spell I was told it was resisted a couple times with lower magic resist but 75 charisma.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">Cauldyth</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">Yeah, while MR is nice to have, I wouldn't sacrifice AC or HP for it.  I'll take Crested Spaulders or Crafted Paldrons before a BS Mantle.<P>The only magic based spells that you'll get hit by are Root, Togor's, Force Shock, Fear, Gravity Flux, and Charm.  I don't think I've had a single Root, Togor's, Fear, or Force Shock stick on me in months.  Gravity Flux and Charm are only available to a handful of creatures in the whole game.  All the really painful spells are cold and fire based.<P><BR>Cauldyth Arranen<BR>Wood Elf Warrior<BR>Povar<BR><p>[This message has been edited by Cauldyth (edited February 14, 2000).]</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">PackMan97</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">Cauldyth - That's what a Evil Eye bag is for...just haul the stuff around and equip as necessary. <P>I agree for everyday combat I wear Crafted Pauldrons and only throw on the BS Mantle when I'm fighting someplace with a HIGH concentration of casters (aka Paw, Mistmoore)...places like KK or L Guk I rarely equip my MR gear.<P>It's just nice to have the OPTION to switch gear in and out as the situation dictates. I also rarely pull it out if there is a Bard in the group =)<P>Anyways...with items like the Runed Bone Fork and MM Shield you gain +20 MR, +10 cold/fire/disease/poison....so it is still worth it fighting any type of caster =)<P>Really it all boils down to who you want advice from? A gnome with a 106 combat INT, or a pretty boy Wood Elf? You decide.<P>-wuf</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">Cauldyth</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica"><BR>Yeah, thank god for weight reducing containers.  Without them, us weaker warriors would have to run to the bank between pulls to change gear. =)<P>And you'll get no argument from me on the Runed Bone Fork.  Great item, and only goes in my backpack when I'm either pulling (need a bow) or absolutely sure there won't be any casters..<P><BR>Cauldyth Arranen<BR>Wood Elf Warrior<BR>Povar<BR></FONT></TD></TR></TABLE></td></tr></table> 
